  "text": "Following the tradition in the PIB literature, explicit PIB was calculated by subtracting the standardized score of the adult-informant index of competence from the standardized score of the child's self-report on the SPPC [CITATION_1] . Implicit PIB was calculated by subtracting the standardized score of the adult-informant index of competence from the standardized score of the child's IAT D score. We note that as an alternative, [CITATION_2] proposed a regression model to calculate PIB. However, because this study examines a novel type of PIB, using an implicit measure, we used the standardized discrepancy score for a more intuitive interpretation of results.",
